SESSION--TO--SESSION

⚠️ Disclaimer

We are not responsible for any kind of misuse or damage caused by this program. Use this tool at your own risk!

🎯 Introduction

SESSION--TO--SESSION is an interactive command-line tool designed to simplify network-related tasks through a user-friendly, menu-based interface. 
The script is useful for quickly establishing terminal-to-terminal connections, performing file transfers, and interacting with network services.
This script streamlines workflows by integrating SSH, FTP, and Netcat connections into a single environment, enhancing productivity and ease of use for both beginners and experienced users.



🔧 Features

--System Information --

Optionally displays the local IP address of the system running the script.

--Network Tools--

SSH Connection :

Connect to remote servers using SSH.
Customizable username, server IP/hostname, and port selection (22 or 8022).
Review and modify connection details before executing.

FTP Connection :

Connect to FTP servers by providing the server IP or hostname.
Simple editing options for server details before connection.
Netcat (NC) Connection:

Multiple functionalities :

Listen on a specified port for incoming connections.
Send files to a target IP over a chosen port.
Receive files by listening on a designated port.
Options to review and edit inputs before execution.



🚀 Installation

To install SESSION--TO--SESSION, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:

>git clone 

>cd 

>chmod +x main



📦 Install Required Packages

Ensure the following packages are installed :

ssh
ftp
netcat

Install them using your package manager [ manualy ]

# For Debian/Ubuntu

sudo apt install openssh-client ftp netcat

For auto installation run the distro-name

# For Debian/Ubuntu

🏃 Run Command

./session


📋 Tool Categories

SESSION--TO--SESSION is divided into the following categories:

SSH Connection : Quickly connect to remote servers.

FTP Connection : Manage FTP server connections.

Netcat Connection : Simplified file transfer and listening.

System Information : Display system IP address.


🧑‍💻 Used For :

System Administrators: Easily access common network utilities without typing complex commands repeatedly.

Beginners: A great tool for learning and practicing basic networking commands in a structured environment.

Productivity Enthusiasts: Streamline workflows by integrating multiple tools under one menu for easier navigation and task execution.


